When using Sun's WorkShop compiler, the bogofilter compile will fail.
Sun's WorkShop compiler does now allow for C++-style (//) comments in C
code. There is a workaround: add -xCC to the environment variable
CFLAGS, example:

env CFLAGS="-O -xCC" CC="/opt/SUNWspro/bin/cc" ksh ./configure \
  --with-db=/usr/local/BerkeleyDB.3.2/

Adjust the SUNWspro and BerkeleyDB paths if necessary.
